  "response_text": "A light-skinned girl, roughly preteen age, fills the screen in a dreamy, slightly blurred close-up. She is looking downward, as if leaning over the viewer, with her hair floating upward around her face. Her expression is calm and pleased, almost smiling. The image flickers between normal color and very bright, washed-out flashes, sometimes turning her face nearly white from the glare. At moments she appears upside down against a pale blue sky, reinforcing the feeling of being in motion or suspended in the air.\n\nThe same girl remains close to the viewer, now more clearly wearing a reddish-pink top. Her arms are raised on either side, and her hair streams upward and backward, suggesting fast movement. She looks down with a small smile, then with a more focused, excited expression. The background is mostly open blue sky, with the image still soft and overexposed in places.\n\nThe scene shifts into the forward view of a roller coaster track. Orange rails stretch straight ahead into a structure of blue and metal supports, with greenery and shadows rushing past on both sides. The track narrows into the distance, creating a tunnel-like sense of speed.\n\nThe ride is then revealed from the front. Two girls sit side by side in the front row of a roller coaster car. On the left is a Black girl, likely an older child or young teen, wearing a bright pink shirt under a light-colored open jacket. On the right is the light-skinned girl in a pinkish-red top with striped long sleeves. Both have their hair blown back by the motion. They are laughing and shouting with excitement, their faces open-mouthed and joyful. Behind them, other riders fill the coaster cars, some with arms raised. The coaster emerges from a dark opening into sunlight, with a curved, concrete-like structure and plants around the entrance.\n\nAs the car continues, the two girls lift their hands higher. The girl on the right looks toward the girl on the left, smiling broadly, while the girl on the left faces forward, laughing. The sky opens bright blue above them. Other riders in the background wave their arms. The front edge of the coaster car forms a yellow band along the bottom of the image.\n\nThe imagery alternates between the girls’ excited faces and wider views of the orange roller coaster track climbing and curving through a web of blue supports. Several moments are layered together in translucent overlays: the girls laughing in the foreground, the track and support beams ghosted across the sky, and riders’ raised arms blending into the structure. The effect makes the ride feel fast, dizzying, and exhilarating.\n\nLarge white graphic shapes briefly slide over the picture, including a bold blocky lowercase letter-like form, partly covering the girls and the coaster. Then scattered white letters swirl in a curved path across the sky and over the roller coaster structure, gradually forming readable information.\n\nThe final view holds on the two girls still riding together, smiling and cheering with their arms up. The roller coaster cars angle behind them on the left, packed with riders. Across the top, large white text reads “helpyourcommunity.org.” Beneath it, centered in dark blue, is the phone number “1-877-KIDS-313.” Along the bottom, the Ad Council logo appears at the left, and small text reads “Office of National Drug Control Policy.” A small red heart-shaped anti-drug campaign logo remains at the lower right.",
